context: In <a0_0><b5_0>1880<b5_0/><a0_0/>, the newspapers News and Observer combined to form <a1_0>The News & Observer<a1_0/>. It remains Raleigh's primary daily newspaper. <a2_0>The North Carolina College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts,<a2_0/> now known as North Carolina State University, was founded as a land-grant college in <a3_0><b8_0>1887<b8_0/><a3_0/>. The city's Rex Hospital opened in <b7_0>1889<b7_0/> and included the state's first nursing school. The Baptist Women's College, now known as <b6_0>Meredith College<b6_0/>, opened in <a4_0>1891<a4_0/>, and in <b9_0>1898<b9_0/>, The Academy of Music, a private music conservatory, was established.
